The paper deals with image recognition using deep learning neural networks, specifically for recognizing historical letters carved on stone walls. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of capsule networks, which is a relatively new and emerging area of research in deep learning, making it likely to fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves pre-processing and data augmentation techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
